parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A transmission fluid leak can cause the transmission to fail, leading to loss of power, loss of vehicle control, and potential accidents.
symptoms: Transmission fluid leaking from the engine
transmission failure
loss of power
difficulty shifting gears
unusual noises or vibrations from the transmission.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A failed valve cover gasket can cause oil leaks, leading to engine damage, loss of power, and potential engine failure.
symptoms: Oil leaking from the valve cover
oil spots under the vehicle
engine noise or vibration
decreased engine performance
engine stalling or failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Intake and Valve Cover Gasket Failures
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failed intake and valve cover gaskets can cause oil leaks, leading to engine damage, loss of power, and potential engine failure.
symptoms: Oil leaking from the intake and valve cover
oil spots under the vehicle
engine noise or vibration
decreased engine performance
engine stalling or failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature wear of the front brake pads can lead to reduced stopping power, increased stopping distances, and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: Vibration or pulsation when applying the brakes
squealing or grinding noise when applying the brakes
excessive brake dust
uneven brake pad wear
brake warning lights or messages on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake failure can cause loss of vehicle control, increased stopping distances, and potentially lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Sudden loss of braking power
inability to stop the vehicle
brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal travels farther than usual before engaging
warning lights or messages on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front hub assembly can cause the wheel to become loose, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries.
symptoms: The front wheel feels loose or wobbly
the vehicle vibrates or shakes while driving
the front wheel makes abnormal noises
the front hub assembly breaks or cracks
the front bushings fail or wear out prematurely.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the alternator can cause the battery to drain, leading to a loss of electrical power and potentially leaving the driver stranded. In extreme cases, it can also cause the engine to stall, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The battery warning light is illuminated on the dashboard
the vehicle's electrical systems (e.g.
radio
lights) malfunction or shut down
the engine stalls or has difficulty starting
the alternator belt is worn or broken.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the starter motor can make it difficult or impossible to start the engine, leaving the driver stranded and potentially causing inconvenience or safety risks.
symptoms: The engine is difficult to start or will not start at all
the starter motor makes a clicking sound but the engine does not turn over
the starter motor is excessively loud or produces a grinding noise.
